these two sides, glue them.

00:07:14.320 --> 00:07:16.030
Now you have a cylinder.

00:07:16.030 --> 00:07:19.630
And now you're supposed to
glue this end to the first end.

00:07:19.630 --> 00:07:24.530
So you glue them like that, and
you form something like this.

00:07:24.530 --> 00:07:25.550
So here is a torus.

00:07:28.840 --> 00:07:33.550
Now we try to put the
magnetic field on this torus.

00:07:33.550 --> 00:07:37.720
So you could say,
well, this is x and y.

00:07:37.720 --> 00:07:38.570
There is a torus.

00:07:38.570 --> 00:07:39.820
There's the z-direction.

00:07:39.820 --> 00:07:41.470
Let's put the
magnetic field that

00:07:41.470 --> 00:07:44.770
goes through the torus
in the z-direction.

00:07:44.770 --> 00:07:46.090
B z.

00:07:46.090 --> 00:07:47.770
B in the z-direction.

00:07:52.700 --> 00:07:55.760
And we'll put a constant
one, B constant.

00:07:55.760 --> 00:08:01.280
So it's time-independent
and space-independent.

00:08:01.280 --> 00:08:06.800
And then you say, OK, let's
look at my Maxwell's equations.

00:08:06.800 --> 00:08:09.330
Divergence of B equals 0.

00:08:09.330 --> 00:08:10.190
