00:16:20.760 --> 00:16:22.770
is xy--

00:16:22.770 --> 00:16:26.880
it's physically the same point--

00:16:26.880 --> 00:16:35.610
plus the gradient of lambda, in
this case would be dy lambda.

00:16:35.610 --> 00:16:36.210
OK.

00:16:36.210 --> 00:16:39.180
Now we have to find
the gauge parameter.

00:16:39.180 --> 00:16:43.740
To show that they're
gauge-equivalent here and here,

00:16:43.740 --> 00:16:46.380
I must find the gauge parameter.

00:16:46.380 --> 00:16:49.290
That's the lambda.

00:16:49.290 --> 00:16:51.640
So let's do the formula here.

00:16:51.640 --> 00:16:54.000
This is B0.

00:16:54.000 --> 00:16:56.640
There's a formula
here, B0 times x.

00:16:56.640 --> 00:17:04.109
So x plus Lx times x plus
