And even though we write
A prime as A D lambda,

00:19:37.020 --> 00:19:39.330
this term can be
written in terms

00:19:39.330 --> 00:19:45.760
of U. U is the master quantity
that has all the information.

00:19:45.760 --> 00:19:56.820
In fact, D lambda is roughly
U minus 1 gradient of U,

00:19:56.820 --> 00:19:58.770
up to a series of factors.

00:19:58.770 --> 00:20:02.220
So everything
depends on U. So we

00:20:02.220 --> 00:20:06.210
don't have to worry too
much if lambda is not

00:20:06.210 --> 00:20:08.700
well-defined on the torus.

00:20:08.700 --> 00:20:11.610
What has to be
well-defined on the torus

00:20:11.610 --> 00:20:17.100
is U, the exponential of lambda.

00:20:17.100 --> 00:20:25.690
And that, it's a saver, because
U, now, is e to the i q.

00:20:25.690 --> 00:20:33.990
Lambda is B0 Lxy over h bar c.

00:20:33.990 --> 00:20:40.830
That's U. And U will be
well-defined on the torus

00:20:40.830 --> 00:20:49.120
if, when you change y plus y
plus L y, this doesn't change.

00:20:49.120 --> 00:20:56.110
And for that, this whole thing,
when you change y by L y,

00:20:56.110 --> 00:21:00.550
must change by a factor of 2 pi.

00:21:00.550 --> 00:21:04.710
So if-- you see, you're
living dangerously with this.

00:21:04.710 --> 00:21:07.420
It just doesn't want
to exist on a torus.

00:21:07.420 --> 00:21:12.430
But if this happens to
be equal to 2 pi n--

00:21:12.430 --> 00:21:23.670
so if you have q B0 Lx Ly
over hc equal to 2 pi n,

00:21:23.670 --> 00:21:25.580
everything is OK.

00:21:25.580 --> 00:21:31.720
That thing, when you
change y for y plus L y,

00:21:31.720 --> 00:21:35.350
this whole exponent
changes by 2 pi n.

00:21:35.350 --> 00:21:37.620
And i times 2 pi n is 1.

00:21:37.620 --> 00:21:42.940
So U is well-defined
on the torus.

00:21:42.940 --> 00:21:44.540
So we're almost there.

00:21:44.540 --> 00:21:45.770
Here it is.

00:21:45.770 --> 00:21:51.550
B0-- there is a quantization.

00:21:51.550 --> 00:22:05.330
B0 times the area of the
torus is equal to 2 pi n--

00:22:05.330 --> 00:22:17.310
pi n-- hc over q n.

00:22:17.310 --> 00:22:23.670
So you cannot have
arbitrary magnetic field.

00:22:23.670 --> 00:22:28.760
The magnetic field is such
that the flux is quantized.

00:22:28.760 --> 00:22:31.910
So here is the
illustration of an example

00:22:31.910 --> 00:22:35.270
I wanted to mention
from the beginning,

00:22:35.270 --> 00:22:39.860
that if you have a magnetic
field that solves Maxwell's

00:22:39.860 --> 00:22:41.570
equations, you're not done.

00:22:41.570 --> 00:22:43.310
You have to find potentials.

00:22:43.310 --> 00:22:45.900
And sometimes there are
funny things happening.

00:22:45.900 --> 00:22:48.200
And in particular,
here is the funny thing

00:22:48.200 --> 00:22:51.470
that has happened
here, is that in order

00:22:51.470 --> 00:22:55.790
to have a well-defined vector
potential on the torus,

00:22:55.790 --> 00:22:59.600
you've been forced to
quantize the magnetic field.

00:22:59.600 --> 00:23:05.960
And B0 times A is
equal to phi, the flux.

00:23:10.250 --> 00:23:15.500
And this flux is a multiple
of this quantity, which

00:23:15.500 --> 00:23:19.220
is sometimes called
the quantum of flux,

00:23:19.220 --> 00:23:22.400
the least possible flux.

00:23:22.400 --> 00:23:24.020
n, the flux quantum.

00:23:30.390 --> 00:23:36.660
So this flux quantum, it is
a famous number, in fact.

00:23:36.660 --> 00:23:38.870
I have it somewhere here.

00:23:46.750 --> 00:23:48.160
Somewhere in my notes.

00:23:48.160 --> 00:23:50.050
Yes, here it is.

00:23:50.050 --> 00:23:56.230
Phi 0 for electrons,
for q equal to e--

00:23:56.230 --> 00:24:02.470
phi 0-- these are
units you seldom use.

00:24:02.470 --> 00:24:12.560
But it's about 2.068 times
10 to the minus 15 webers.

00:24:15.250 --> 00:24:17.110
Who knows what a weber is?

00:24:20.200 --> 00:24:32.420
Or 2.068 times 10 to
the minus 7 Maxwells.

00:24:35.520 --> 00:24:38.880
Anybody know what a Maxwell is?

00:24:38.880 --> 00:24:42.310
OK, a weber is a unit of flux.

00:24:42.310 --> 00:24:45.590
It's tesla times meter squared.

00:24:45.590 --> 00:24:48.040
That's far too big.

00:24:48.040 --> 00:24:53.070
The Maxwell, it's a
more natural thing.

00:24:53.070 --> 00:24:59.880
Maxwell is gauss times
centimeters squared.

00:24:59.880 --> 00:25:02.460
So, you know, the magnetic
field of the Earth

00:25:02.460 --> 00:25:04.350
is about half a gauss.

00:25:04.350 --> 00:25:07.060
A centimeter square
you can imagine.

00:25:07.060 --> 00:25:10.230
And that's the value of
the flux quantum, which

00:25:10.230 --> 00:25:15.020
will have a role later for us.

